    { id: 15359, title: "Questions 59-61", text: "Thanks for calling Hang's Metal Recycling Company. How can I help you? Hi. I'm with Shannak Construction Company. We've got a lot of brass metal scrap from a recent remodeling job. Are you currently buying metal scrap? Yes, we are. We currently pay two dollars a pound. Oh, there's another recycling center that pays two dollars and twenty-five cents a pound. Would you be willing to match their price? Yes, we have a price-match guarantee. Great. I'll bring the metal to you this afternoon, then." },
    { id: 15362, title: "Questions 62-64", text: "Hi. I just got off the phone with management. They're not happy. The construction of the train tunnel isn't progressing fast enough. Yeah, I'm not surprised. The drilling is done now. The thing is, we can't start installing the support columns until we have all the materials for the concrete. When are the materials going to get here? A week, maybe two. Let's see if the shipment can be expedited. Can you do that? Sure. I'll call the supplier to ask about getting it here sooner. In the meantime, I'm going to write an e-mail to management to explain how we're attempting to resolve the situation." },
    { id: 15365, title: "Questions 65-67", text: "The city just posted its new parking rates, and we need to talk about how they'll affect our restaurant's food delivery service. I'm worried we'll lose money because we'll need to pay more for parking while the delivery driver takes the food to customers. Wow. Parking in our main delivery area is up to fifteen dollars an hour? That is a problem. But offering free delivery attracts a lot of business. What else can we do to lower expenses? We could start using bicycle delivery whenever possible. That should help. Good idea. I'll talk to our drivers to see who's willing to switch to bicycle deliveries for customers nearby. Some people really like the exercise." },
    { id: 15368, title: "Questions 68-70", text: "When customers walk into Southern Regional Bank, I want them to feel confident about entrusting their money to us. As I mentioned the last time we met, I'm hoping your interior design firm can give our lobby a more polished, professional look. Our proposal does just that. Here—take a look. The cover page includes a summary of the renovations. Hmm. Do you really think we need skylights? That would be a big expense. There aren't many windows in your lobby, so it's the best way to bring more natural light into the room. Besides, our proposed renovations would actually come in under budget. If you turn to page four, you'll see the cost breakdown." }
